<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFBFFFE56DC2FDD4FE8FA9B5" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFBFFFE56DC2FDD4FE8FA9B5" blockId="27.[178,1086,549,695]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">
Diagnosis: Distinguishable from superficially similar specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="93C57788FFBFFFE56E92FDD4FEBCA97E" authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pilosirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonicus">
<emphasis id="66B1D019FFBFFFE56E92FDD4FEBCA97E" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">Pilosirus amazonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having much narrower flavotestaceous lines on the pronotal disc. Also, the pronotal tubercle is more acute than it is in 
<emphasis id="66B1D019FFBFFFE56FDFFD19FCB3A99B" box="[687,806,644,665]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">amazonicus</emphasis>
specimens (compare 
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFFBFFFE5697BFD1EFE9AA9B5" captionStart="Figs 133-144" captionStartId="40.[178,218,1358,1380]" captionTargetBox="[207,1052,231,1340]" captionTargetId="figure-1@40.[178,1084,212,1340]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figs 133-144: Aedeagi (133-140), Pronota (141-142), and Female mesodermal female reproductive organs (143-144). (133) Artoadenus similus phallus; (134) A. similus tegmen; (135) Tarandocerus auratus phallus; (136) T. auratus tegmen; (137) T. mexicanus phallus; (138) T. mexicanus tegmen; (139) T. testaceiceps phallus; (140) T. testaceiceps tegmen; (141) Pilosirus amazonicus; (142) P. versus; (143) Ambonoides retinoides female internal reproductive organs; (144) A. retinoides bursal plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5294880" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5294880/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">Figs. 141, 142</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFBFFFE56DC2FD5BFC67A8AB" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540" type="description">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFBFFFE56DC2FD5BFC67A8AB" blockId="27.[178,1086,710,937]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">
Description: Size: Length 7.0 mm; width 2.0 mm. Form: As in 
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFFBFFFE56EE8FD5BFC64A9DE" box="[920,1009,710,732]" captionStart="Figs 161-164" captionStartId="52.[178,218,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-59@52.[178,1085,212,1498]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Figs 161-164: Habitus illustrations of (161) Pilosirus fasciatus, holotype; (162) P. versus, holotype; (163) Platynoptera carti, holotype; (164) Platynoptera flavohumeralis, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282519/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">Fig. 162</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium mostly black, clypeus and cranial venter flavotestaceous; pronotum mostly black, upper sides narrowly flavotestaceous; mesoscutellum black; elytra black. Head: Antennal capitulum long (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFFBFFFE56CB0FC83FD98A836" box="[448,525,798,820]" captionStart="Figs 81-86" captionStartId="22.[178,218,1223,1245]" captionTargetBox="[192,1067,240,1173]" captionTargetId="figure-1@22.[178,1085,212,1205]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figs 81-86: Antennae. (81) Platynoptera ochreata, female; (82) Artoadenus similus, male; (83) Tarandocerus auratus, male; (84) T. mexicanus, male; (85) T. testaceiceps, male; (86) Pilosirus versus, female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5294868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5294868/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">Fig. 86</figureCitation>
), each capitular antennomere not as long as combined length of funicular antennomeres; antennal carina very prominent; EW/FW 12/15. Thorax: Pronotal anterior margin not projected at middle, side margin of disc with subacute tubercle; PW/PL 45/45; elytral disc not strongly deflexed at sides, carina not present; EL/EW 160/30. Abdomen: Female pygidium not incised at distal margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFBFFFE56DC2FC25FCF9A8CC" box="[178,876,952,974]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFBFFFE56DC2FC25FCF9A8CC" blockId="27.[178,876,952,974]" box="[178,876,952,974]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">
Distribution (
<figureCitation id="CCFE108EFFBFFFE56CEAFC25FE61A8CC" box="[410,500,952,974]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="57.[178,210,1399,1421]" captionTargetBox="[203,1066,235,1376]" captionTargetId="figure-1@57.[178,1085,212,1389]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="Fig. 175: Geographic distribution of species as noted." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282537" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282537/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">Fig. 175</figureCitation>
): Known only from the 
<typeStatus id="8B7EB2A9FFBFFFE56F97FC24FC86A8CC" box="[743,787,953,974]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1CDF5F80FFBFFFE56DC2FC43FDC5AF13" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="547A0C0BFFBFFFE56DC2FC43FDC5AF13" blockId="27.[178,1085,990,1041]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">
Etymology: The trivial name, 
<emphasis id="66B1D019FFBFFFE56F5CFC43FDF9A8F1" box="[556,620,990,1011]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">versus</emphasis>
(= line), is a Latin noun. I refer to the narrow flavotestaceous line on the pronotal disc.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
